# arc's own coordination state. The human operator's call (2026-07-17): the WHOLE
# .arc travels by `arc export`/`arc import`, never by git — roles/ included. This
# rule lives at the repo root (not self-ignored inside .arc) on purpose: it is the
# half that TRAVELS, so a fresh clone inherits the rule instead of re-committing
# charters the moment someone runs `git add -A`.
.arc/
